SLAVEA CHANKOVA and Kenneth Cukier investigate the ways in which SARS-CoV-2, the virus which causes covid-19, wears the body down. Apart from pneumonia, there are other facets to the disease that are less understood such as damage to the kidneys, blood vessels and heart. And, how does covid-19 continue to harm the body—and patients' mental health— in the long term? Runtime: 26 min  Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify |Google | Stitcher | TuneIn Please subscribe to The Economist for full access to print, digital and audio editions: www.economist.com/podcastoffer